12
[p 
	"Having the powers of flight and spindashing, Tails blasts through Sonic 1, leaving 
	[a href=/1847S 
		"Sonic
	]a
	" and even the mighty 
	[a href=/1384S 
		"Knuckles
	]a
	" eating dust in almost all levels of the game. This movie was made with Pu7o's 
	[a class=extlink href=http://info.sonicretro.org/Tails_in_Sonic_1 rel=nofollow 
		"Tails in Sonic 1
	]a
	" hack, version 2.1.1.
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	" Game objectives
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" Emulator used: Gens 9Z
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Aims for fastest time
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Takes no damage
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Abuses programming errors
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Ignores delays caused by bonus effects
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h3 
	" Comments
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"This impressive hack by Pu7o places Tails into Sonic the Hedgehog 1. Being a marked improvement (and complete rewrite) over the earlier version by drx, it underwent two revisions during the making of this movie to make Tails' flight and swimming work exactly like they do in Sonic 3 and Sonic 3 & Knuckles.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"This was based on the 
	[a href=/1847S 
		"Sonic
	]a
	" and the 
	[a href=/1384S 
		"Knuckles
	]a
	" runs of Sonic 1. But differences between Tails and Sonic (spindash, flight and even hitbox size) and between Tails and Knuckles (flight vs. glide/climb) made some routes impossible while enabling others. Overall, the two-tailed game wrecker blasts through the game leaving everyone else far behind.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The biggest time saver was the abuse of the Sonic 3 enforced screen boundary for Tails' flight: whenever you start flight (or boost) at or above the top of the stage, vertical speed is set to zero, preventing horizontal speed loss due to drag. Thus, you can maintain a given altitude and horizontal speed for as long as Tails' can fly. The use of this technique is marked below.
	$LF
]p
